.TH BITCOIN-CLI "1" "February 2015" "becoin-cli 0.10" 
.SH NAME
becoin-cli \- a remote procedure call client for BeCoin Core. 
.SH SYNOPSIS
becoin-cli [options] <command> [params] \- Send command to BeCoin Core. 
.TP
becoin-cli [options] help \- Asks BeCoin Core for a list of supported commands.
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual page documents the becoin-cli program. becoin-cli is an RPC client used to send commands to BeCoin Core.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-?\fR
Show the help message.
.TP
\fB\-conf=\fR<file>
Specify configuration file (default: becoin.conf).
.TP
\fB\-datadir=\fR<dir>
Specify data directory.
.TP
\fB\-testnet\fR
Connect to a BeCoin Core instance running in testnet mode.
.TP
\fB\-regtest\fR
Connect to a BeCoin Core instance running in regtest mode (see documentation for -regtest on becoind).
.TP
\fB\-rpcuser=\fR<user>
Username for JSON\-RPC connections.
.TP
\fB\-rpcpassword=\fR<pw>
Password for JSON\-RPC connections.
.TP
\fB\-rpcport=\fR<port>
Listen for JSON\-RPC connections on <port> (default: 8332 or testnet: 18332).
.TP
\fB\-rpcconnect=\fR<ip>
Send commands to node running on <ip> (default: 127.0.0.1).
.TP
\fB\-rpcssl\fR=\fI1\fR
Use OpenSSL (https) for JSON\-RPC connections (see the BeCoin Wiki for SSL setup instructions).

.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBbecoind\fP, \fBbecoin.conf\fP
